1. Expansion Overview
This document extends the Attention-Aware Study Assistant with a full Video Intelligence layer. The existing system already tracks cognitive fatigue during text-based learning. This expansion introduces the same adaptive fatigue loop to video-based learning, adds YouTube-powered content discovery, and integrates your personal transcription-summary model as a graceful fallback when fatigue crosses a critical threshold.

The design philosophy is the same as the core system: observe signals, reason about learner state, act with the least-friction adaptation. For video, the signals are different — interaction with the player is the telemetry — but the agentic loop is identical.

1.1 How Video Telemetry Signals Fatigue
Unlike keystroke patterns, video watching produces behavioural signals through player interactions:

Player Event	Fatigue Signal Direction	Interpretation
Speed increased (1x → 1.5x → 2x)	↓  LOWER fatigue	Learner is engaged and confident — content is easy to absorb at speed
Skip forward (jumped ahead)	↓  LOWER fatigue	Learner already knows the material — low cognitive load
Pause (short, < 10 sec)	→  NEUTRAL	Natural pause, note-taking, or distraction — ambiguous
Pause (long, > 30 sec)	↑  HIGHER fatigue	Learner zoned out or overwhelmed — disengagement signal
Speed decreased (2x → 1x)	↑  HIGHER fatigue	Content became difficult or confusing — cognitive load rising
Seek backward / replay segment	↑↑  HIGH fatigue	Strong confusion signal — learner could not process the segment first time
Repeated backward seeks on same spot	↑↑↑  CRITICAL	Triggers summary fallback — fatigue threshold breached

 
2. New Microservices (SVC-08 to SVC-10)
Three new services extend the existing 7-service architecture. They slot in cleanly: the Orchestrator Agent (SVC-05) is updated to route video interactions through these new services while all existing text-learning services remain untouched.

SVC-08  ·  Video Fatigue Monitor Agent
file: video_fatigue_monitor.py  ·  port: 8006

Receives a stream of player events from the Streamlit video component (or a YouTube iframe tracker) and maintains a rolling fatigue score for the current video session. This is the video-specific equivalent of SVC-01 (Attention Monitor).

What it does

Inputs	Outputs
•	event_type (play / pause / seek / speed_change)
•	current_position_sec (int)
•	playback_rate (float, e.g. 1.5)
•	seek_delta_sec (negative = backward seek)
•	session_id (string)	•	score: float 0–1
•	label: ENGAGED / NEUTRAL / STRUGGLING / CRITICAL
•	trigger_summary: bool
•	current_position_sec: int
•	recommended_action: string

Tech Stack	Python · FastAPI · in-memory dict (session queues) · Pydantic
Key Endpoints	POST /video-event  |  GET /video-history/{session_id}  |  POST /reset/{session_id}

SVC-09  ·  YouTube Recommender Agent
file: youtube_recommender.py  ·  port: 8007

Takes the learner's current study topic (already stored in the Learner Profile) and fetches the 3 most relevant YouTube videos using the YouTube Data API v3. Applies a relevance + quality filter (view count, duration cap, channel credibility) before returning results. Passes video metadata to the Orchestrator so the Streamlit UI can embed the player directly.

What it does

Inputs	Outputs
•	topic (string, from Learner Profile)
•	difficulty_level (int 1–5)
•	session_id (string)
•	YOUTUBE_API_KEY (env var)	•	video_id (YouTube ID string)
•	title, channel, duration_sec
•	thumbnail_url, youtube_url
•	relevance_score (float)

Tech Stack	Python · FastAPI · google-api-python-client · Anthropic SDK (query optimisation)
External APIs	YouTube Data API v3 (free, 10,000 units/day quota)  ·  Anthropic Claude API
Key Endpoints	POST /recommend  |  GET /cached/{session_id}

SVC-10  ·  Transcription Summary Agent
file: transcription_summary.py  ·  port: 8008

The fatigue fallback service. When Video Fatigue Monitor signals CRITICAL state, this service takes over. It loads your existing transcription model from the /transcriber folder, runs it on the video (or its cached transcript), and uses Claude to generate a structured, learner-friendly summary. The learner reads the summary instead of watching the rest of the video — dramatically reducing cognitive load.

What it does

Inputs	Outputs
•	video_id (YouTube ID)
•	from_position_sec (int)
•	to_position_sec (int)
•	topic (string)
•	session_id (string)
•	Your transcriber model at /transcriber/transcriber.py	•	summary_markdown (Markdown string)
•	key_concepts (list of strings)
•	estimated_read_sec (int)
•	video_section_covered (e.g. '4:20 – 9:00')
•	prerequisite_gaps (list of strings)

Tech Stack	Python · FastAPI · Your transcriber module · Anthropic SDK (summarisation) · SQLite cache
Your model path	/transcriber/transcriber.py  — drop your model here; the service imports it on startup
Key Endpoints	POST /summarise  |  GET /cached/{video_id}  |  GET /health
 
3. Orchestrator Updates — Video Routing Logic
The existing Orchestrator (SVC-05, port 8000) gains a new /video-interact endpoint and updated routing logic. All existing /interact behaviour remains unchanged — this is purely additive.

3.1 New Endpoint: POST /video-interact
Called by Streamlit on every video player event. Runs the same 4-step ReAct loop but with video-specific agents:

Step	Agent Called	What Happens
OBSERVE	SVC-08 Video Fatigue Monitor	Post the player event (seek, speed, pause). Receive fatigue score + trigger_summary flag.
REASON	SVC-02 Learner Profiler	Fetch learner profile. Combine video fatigue with existing text-session fatigue for a unified cognitive state.
ACT	SVC-10 or adaptive player signal	If trigger_summary=true → call SVC-10, return summary. Otherwise return recommended_action (e.g. 'suggest_speed_down', 'none').
REFLECT	SVC-02 + SVC-06	Update learner profile with video fatigue data. Log event to Data Store for session summary.

3.2 Fatigue Threshold Decision Table
Video Fatigue Label	Score Range	Orchestrator Action	Returned to UI
ENGAGED	0.0 – 0.25	No intervention — let video play	{ action: 'none' }
NEUTRAL	0.25 – 0.50	No intervention	{ action: 'none' }
STRUGGLING	0.50 – 0.75	Show non-intrusive tip: 'Slow down or take a note?'	{ action: 'suggest_slowdown', message: '...' }
CRITICAL	0.75 – 1.0	Trigger SVC-10 immediately. Pause video player. Show summary.	{ action: 'show_summary', summary: SummaryResult }
 
